text.paragraph:
                     Cardiovascular – cardiac arrhythmia, hypotension, 
peripheral circulatory collapse, bradycardia, sinus node dysfunction with severe 
bradycardia (which may result in syncope);

                     Gastrointestinal - anorexia, nausea, vomiting, 
diarrhea, gastritis, salivary gland swelling, abdominal pain, excessive 
salivation, flatulence, indigestion;

                     Genitourinary - glycosuria, decreased creatinine 
clearance, albuminuria, oliguria, and symptoms of nephrogenic diabetes insipidus 
including polyuria, thirst and polydipsia;
